<!--NOTE: This is NOT the same thing as a "Troglodyte". "Troglobite" applies to animals, some living, whereas "Troglodyte" applies to cave-men.-->
{{Move to Wiktionary}}
A '''troglobite''' is an [[animal]] that lives entirely in the dark parts of [[cave]]s. Such animals are specifically adapted to life in total darkness, and may have no function [[eye]]s or have no [[pigmentation]]. Examples include the [[blind cave fish]] and [[cave cricket]]s.

